3
00:01:57,390 --> 00:02:01,360
That's when it happened!
That's when I said to him,

4
00:02:01,360 --> 00:02:03,900
"You bowlegged bastard!"

5
00:02:03,900 --> 00:02:05,350
Ever since that day,

6
00:02:05,350 --> 00:02:08,520
the world's crabs have been
insecure about being bowlegged.

7
00:02:10,190 --> 00:02:11,990
So that's why they walk sideways?

8
00:02:11,990 --> 00:02:16,030
Uh-huh. But some of them
would hop backwards instead.

9
00:02:16,030 --> 00:02:17,530
I called them "prawns".

10
00:02:18,660 --> 00:02:20,950
So prawns are just crabs?

11
00:02:20,950 --> 00:02:22,860
Yeah, they're crabs.

12
00:02:24,670 --> 00:02:28,510
Zoro, aren't you just wasting
your energy doing that?

13
00:02:28,510 --> 00:02:29,720
Shut up.

14
00:02:29,720 --> 00:02:32,470
Just leave them be, Nami.

15
00:02:32,470 --> 00:02:36,760
Those guys need to keep busy
so they don't dwell on things.

16
00:02:36,760 --> 00:02:39,470
They're primitive like that. Especially...

17
00:02:42,180 --> 00:02:46,270
that meathead, now that he's
had a taste of the Warlords' strength.

18
00:02:47,310 --> 00:02:49,860
Hey, you, what are you trying to say?

19
00:02:50,350 --> 00:02:51,620
Go ahead and spell it out.

20
00:02:51,620 --> 00:02:53,820
Ah, you want me to say it?

21
00:02:53,820 --> 00:02:58,780
You're scared. You're worried
that Luffy might lose.

22
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:04,120
Who, me?! You calling me scared?!
You're nothing but...

23
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:05,210
fancy eyebrows!

24
00:03:05,210 --> 00:03:08,000
That's it! Now you've done it...

25
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:09,900
Moss Head!

26
00:03:09,900 --> 00:03:10,880
What?!

27
00:03:11,490 --> 00:03:13,350
You wanna go at it?!

28
00:03:15,150 --> 00:03:17,340
Cut it out! This is pointless.

29
00:03:19,090 --> 00:03:23,050
They can't help themselves.
Everyone's a bit wound up.

30
00:03:23,050 --> 00:03:25,280
Now's the time for me,
the vice captain, to–

31
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:27,660
Calm down, everyone.

32
00:03:27,130 --> 00:03:27,660
Huh?

33
00:03:27,660 --> 00:03:30,730
Luffy won't lose. I mean,
we promised him, didn't we?

34
00:03:30,730 --> 00:03:33,440
That we'd be waiting
for him in Alubarna?

35
00:03:33,440 --> 00:03:36,030
You seem more worried
than anyone here!

36
00:03:37,370 --> 00:03:38,180
Ow!

37
00:03:38,180 --> 00:03:40,990
You just worry about the rebellion.

38
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:43,700
Sorry about that, Vivi.

39
00:03:43,700 --> 00:03:46,660
If you have to reassure us,
we're done for.

40
00:03:47,760 --> 00:03:50,740
All right, then switch
your minds over to Alubarna!

41
00:03:50,740 --> 00:03:53,400
Let's go, Pincers!

42
00:03:56,270 --> 00:03:57,250
What's that?

43
00:03:57,250 --> 00:03:58,560
A name for the crab.

44
00:03:59,620 --> 00:04:00,770
"Pincers," you say?

45
00:04:00,770 --> 00:04:02,470
– Got a problem with it?
– Nope. No problem.

46
00:04:12,690 --> 00:04:15,940
Look! Th-There's so much!

47
00:04:17,440 --> 00:04:19,390
The water...

48
00:04:21,030 --> 00:04:23,320
The water is coming forth!

49
00:04:25,370 --> 00:04:27,650
Didn't I tell you, Luffy?

50
00:04:28,830 --> 00:04:30,750
This land is strong.

51
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:36,170
Yuba still lives.

52
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:42,130
Yuba will die...

53
00:04:42,130 --> 00:04:45,600
from that one, final sandstorm.

54
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:50,720
And then, the flame of anger in
the Rebel Army will burn even hotter.

55
00:04:53,520 --> 00:04:58,530
This outmoded compassion for others
will be this land's downfall.

56
00:04:59,990 --> 00:05:03,950
And the same goes for you,
Straw Hat Luffy.

57
00:05:04,610 --> 00:05:08,870
If you had abandoned this useless
compassion, you'd have lived longer.

58
00:05:11,780 --> 00:05:13,710
Water...?

59
00:05:13,710 --> 00:05:17,920
I doubt you still feel
indebted to this water, huh?

60
00:05:30,890 --> 00:05:34,060
What's that? You're still alive?

61
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:57,420
That looks painful. But you'll
be out of your misery soon enough.

62
00:06:06,180 --> 00:06:08,250
Bye, now.

63
00:06:13,030 --> 00:06:15,870
What a waste of my time.

64
00:06:28,420 --> 00:06:34,740
No big deal. Once the dust
subsides, it will rain.

65
00:06:34,740 --> 00:06:36,580
Just like always.

66
00:06:38,750 --> 00:06:42,720
Bring it on! Bring it on, sandstorms—
as often as you dare!

67
00:06:43,220 --> 00:06:47,890
Yuba will never give in to the sand!

68
00:06:56,050 --> 00:06:57,990
Me, go to Alubarna?

69
00:06:59,230 --> 00:07:01,400
To go after the Straw Hat
Pirates, right?

70
00:07:01,400 --> 00:07:04,210
Or should we assist the Royal Army?

71
00:07:04,210 --> 00:07:05,820
It's up to you.

72
00:07:07,060 --> 00:07:10,370
You decide what to do
when you're there.

73
00:07:10,840 --> 00:07:13,620
But that... What do you
mean by that?

74
00:07:14,070 --> 00:07:16,580
You just follow your sense of justice.

75
00:07:17,380 --> 00:07:21,130
Whatever happens,
I'll accept responsibility.

76
00:07:22,850 --> 00:07:24,720
Captain Smoker,
where are you going?

77
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:27,430
Something urgent came up.
I'm heading back to sea.

78
00:07:28,180 --> 00:07:30,680
Stay prepared for my call, Tashigi.

79
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:31,890
Of course.

80
00:07:33,350 --> 00:07:36,350
Keep a close eye on what
becomes of this country.

81
00:07:39,720 --> 00:07:41,860
Whether it endures or crumbles,

82
00:07:41,860 --> 00:07:45,530
these events will herald
the dawn of a new era.

83
00:07:52,490 --> 00:07:55,540
Chief... Chief Petty Officer!

84
00:07:55,540 --> 00:07:57,160
Your orders?

85
00:07:57,160 --> 00:07:57,750
Right...

86
00:08:00,270 --> 00:08:03,940
Keep a close watch on
where this country ends up.

87
00:08:03,940 --> 00:08:06,100
Whether it endures or crumbles,

88
00:08:06,100 --> 00:08:09,760
these events will herald
the dawn of a new era.

89
00:08:13,370 --> 00:08:17,470
We're going after the pirate
Straw Hat Luffy and his crew!

90
00:08:17,470 --> 00:08:21,730
All hands, take up arms!
Prepare to depart for Alubarna!

91
00:08:21,730 --> 00:08:22,440
– Yes, ma'am!
– Yes, ma'am!

92
00:08:24,450 --> 00:08:26,150
Straw Hat Luffy...

93
00:08:35,410 --> 00:08:40,640
Just you wait, Cobra.
We're going to defend Alabasta.

94
00:08:40,640 --> 00:08:43,010
We won't surrender its fate to you!

95
00:08:52,340 --> 00:08:55,480
Ready cannons at the south gate!
Stop dawdling! Hurry!

96
00:08:55,480 --> 00:08:57,850
Bring more cannonballs over here!

97
00:09:01,650 --> 00:09:02,770
Commander Chaka!

98
00:09:03,910 --> 00:09:07,030
The enemy's numbers are said
to be well over two million!

99
00:09:08,240 --> 00:09:12,650
What do you think of His Majesty's
attack on Nanohana?

100
00:09:12,650 --> 00:09:16,520
I have served him for
ten years, so I was quite...

101
00:09:16,520 --> 00:09:19,460
Yeah. There's really no way
anyone could believe it.

102
00:09:20,240 --> 00:09:23,420
I can only presume that
something happened to the king.

103
00:09:25,040 --> 00:09:29,760
And if so, it's all the more reason
why we must not lose this fight.

104
00:09:29,760 --> 00:09:31,680
Do not flinch at the enemy's number.

105
00:09:31,680 --> 00:09:35,600
For the good of the king
and the return of Princess Vivi,

106
00:09:36,100 --> 00:09:38,560
we will defend this country!

107
00:09:39,480 --> 00:09:42,850
Everyone not joining the battle,
take shelter outside the city!

108
00:09:42,850 --> 00:09:45,400
We cannot guarantee
your safety if you stay!

109
00:09:45,400 --> 00:09:49,400
Run! We're going to be
caught in the crossfire!

110
00:09:51,310 --> 00:09:54,370
Things are finally starting
to become hectic, huh?

111
00:09:54,850 --> 00:09:56,660
Speed up this riot, already, ok?

112
00:09:56,660 --> 00:09:58,580
Things are so slow, I can't stand it.

113
00:10:04,490 --> 00:10:07,420
He's a king! He's a king! I don't care!

114
00:10:07,420 --> 00:10:10,580
I can't watch him
much longer, I swear!

115
00:10:10,580 --> 00:10:13,630
Can't take it! Can't, can't,
for crying out loud!

116
00:10:15,760 --> 00:10:18,390
I mean, sure, slipping past
the palace guards

117
00:10:18,390 --> 00:10:22,860
and kidnapping this guy was a mission
that only we could carry out,

118
00:10:22,860 --> 00:10:25,740
but now that's done,
and it's like we're watching paint dry!

119
00:10:25,740 --> 00:10:27,400
Right, Mr. 4?

120
00:10:28,100 --> 00:10:29,270
Did you hear me?

121
00:10:29,270 --> 00:10:32,020
You are so slow
at answering me, seriously!

122
00:10:33,360 --> 00:10:34,950
Ah, my back hurts!
My back! My ba...

123
00:10:34,950 --> 00:10:37,320
Chaka... Koza...

124
00:10:37,760 --> 00:10:42,260
You must stop this conflict. You are
the ones that define this country.

125
00:10:42,260 --> 00:10:44,280
This fight can only bring destruction.

126
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:48,960
Those who lament war...

127
00:10:55,290 --> 00:10:57,300
Those who go to war...

128
00:11:04,480 --> 00:11:06,300
Go on, run away!

129
00:11:08,420 --> 00:11:10,740
Those who incite war...

130
00:11:13,740 --> 00:11:17,000
Those who, knowing the truth,
want to prevent it...

131
00:11:22,680 --> 00:11:25,060
Each of their feelings are at odds,

132
00:11:25,060 --> 00:11:28,170
as they clash in the capital city of Alubarna.

133
00:11:31,590 --> 00:11:34,510
What?! We can't cross
the river with this crab?!

134
00:11:34,510 --> 00:11:38,770
Moving crabs live in the desert,
so they don't take to water.

135
00:11:38,770 --> 00:11:43,480
But it's a crab, right? A crab!
Not a lobster! Do something!

136
00:11:44,230 --> 00:11:46,610
Hey, this is a problem. Not good.

137
00:11:46,610 --> 00:11:47,440
Look here.

138
00:11:48,020 --> 00:11:50,900
If we carelessly swim across
this river, as wide as a sea,

139
00:11:50,900 --> 00:11:53,140
we won't make it in time! And look!

140
00:11:53,140 --> 00:11:56,580
After we cross, there are still
dozens of kilometers of desert!

141
00:11:56,580 --> 00:11:58,820
If this crab can't make it
to the other side,

142
00:11:58,820 --> 00:12:00,740
are we then supposed
to run on foot?!

143
00:12:00,740 --> 00:12:01,660
There's no choice.

144
00:12:01,660 --> 00:12:03,490
There's no way we'll make it in time!

145
00:12:03,490 --> 00:12:05,960
It's absolutely impossible!

146
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:15,170
Uh-oh. Hey, there's the river!

147
00:12:15,170 --> 00:12:17,630
I can see the Sandora River!

148
00:12:16,980 --> 00:12:17,630
What?!

149
00:12:17,630 --> 00:12:20,010
Do something, Pincers!

150
00:12:20,390 --> 00:12:23,100
I know! Pincers loves dancing girls!

151
00:12:25,800 --> 00:12:26,960
Will this do?

152
00:12:26,960 --> 00:12:27,940
Probably.

153
00:12:27,940 --> 00:12:29,140
Holy crap!

154
00:12:31,640 --> 00:12:33,570
Ah, he's looking this way!

155
00:12:36,010 --> 00:12:37,380
We're going faster!

156
00:12:37,380 --> 00:12:40,040
Nami my sweet!

157
00:12:43,680 --> 00:12:45,780
You broke two animals
with this lunacy!

158
00:12:45,780 --> 00:12:48,210
All right, pervy power!

159
00:12:49,420 --> 00:12:53,170
So, how has this
solved anything? Chopper!

160
00:12:59,510 --> 00:13:00,630
Go!

161
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:04,840
He did it!

162
00:13:06,020 --> 00:13:09,560
Hey, now, this crab is incredible!
I don't believe it!

163
00:13:09,560 --> 00:13:11,310
Whoa, way to go!

164
00:13:11,310 --> 00:13:14,320
It's a miracle! Just stay
on the water and run!

165
00:13:14,320 --> 00:13:17,530
Run, run, run all the way! Go!

166
00:13:17,530 --> 00:13:21,700
You can make it! Keep going!
You can do it! This crab can do it!

167
00:13:21,700 --> 00:13:24,770
Hey, what's this?! Am I imagining
things, or are we sinking?

168
00:13:24,770 --> 00:13:26,440
We are sinking!

169
00:13:30,860 --> 00:13:32,370
Stop sinking, you crab!

170
00:13:32,370 --> 00:13:36,000
No time to whine about it.
Keep moving forward.

171
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:38,300
H-Hold on a second!

172
00:13:38,300 --> 00:13:41,970
Aren't there any boats? How many
kilometers to the other shore?

173
00:13:41,970 --> 00:13:43,340
About fifty.

174
00:13:43,340 --> 00:13:44,300
Who can swim that?!

175
00:13:46,560 --> 00:13:48,390
Thank you!

176
00:13:48,390 --> 00:13:50,560
Thank you, Pincers!

177
00:13:50,560 --> 00:13:53,400
This is no time to be
happily waving goodbye!

178
00:13:56,350 --> 00:13:57,940
What?!

179
00:14:00,070 --> 00:14:03,490
It's a rare Sandoran catfish!
They're hardly ever seen!

180
00:14:03,490 --> 00:14:05,810
You don't have to explain that!

181
00:14:06,880 --> 00:14:08,990
Also, humans are their favorite food!

182
00:14:08,990 --> 00:14:11,330
You should have led with that!

183
00:14:20,460 --> 00:14:22,700
Hey, let go! I can't see a thing now!

184
00:14:22,700 --> 00:14:24,470
Chopper, let go!

185
00:14:33,090 --> 00:14:34,810
Kung fu dugongs?!

186
00:14:34,810 --> 00:14:34,850
Kung fu dugongs?!

187
00:14:34,850 --> 00:14:34,890
Kung fu dugongs?!

188
00:14:34,890 --> 00:14:34,930
Kung fu dugongs?!

189
00:14:34,930 --> 00:14:34,970
Kung fu dugongs?!

190
00:14:35,970 --> 00:14:38,370
They say they won't
abandon their senior pupils.

191
00:14:38,370 --> 00:14:41,580
Well, it's not like we're
Luffy's pupils, or anything...

192
00:14:41,580 --> 00:14:43,710
Still, they saved us.

193
00:14:43,710 --> 00:14:46,990
All right, just a little
farther! Hang in there!

194
00:14:46,550 --> 00:14:48,160
Thank you!

195
00:14:48,160 --> 00:14:50,390
Bye-bye!

196
00:14:52,660 --> 00:14:55,120
So far so good.
Will we actually make it?

197
00:14:55,120 --> 00:14:56,610
It's going to be tough.

198
00:14:56,610 --> 00:14:59,330
Even Eyelashes might not
get us there in time.

199
00:14:59,330 --> 00:15:02,740
What's more, he could only carry,
uh... two of us!

200
00:15:02,740 --> 00:15:06,390
And from here on,
Baroque Works could attack us.

201
00:15:06,390 --> 00:15:09,300
Isn't there any way
for all of us to travel together?

202
00:15:17,440 --> 00:15:19,300
Look! Over there!

203
00:15:19,300 --> 00:15:22,730
What, is it the enemy?
A-A-Are they here already?!

204
00:15:25,030 --> 00:15:26,740
N-No! That's...!

205
00:15:27,980 --> 00:15:29,640
Karoo!

206
00:15:30,650 --> 00:15:33,550
And the Supersonic Duck Squad!

207
00:15:35,310 --> 00:15:36,910
You came to get us!

208
00:15:38,200 --> 00:15:39,380
Karoo!

209
00:16:01,270 --> 00:16:05,320
Meat!

210
00:16:12,360 --> 00:16:18,120
As a pirate, I outclass
you in every way!

211
00:16:18,120 --> 00:16:20,060
Yuba will die...

212
00:16:20,060 --> 00:16:24,610
And then, the flame of anger in
the Rebel Army will burn even hotter.

213
00:17:14,290 --> 00:17:17,180
Thank... you...

214
00:17:22,340 --> 00:17:23,730
Why do you fight?

215
00:17:29,490 --> 00:17:31,700
People like you,
who carry the name "D"?

216
00:17:33,870 --> 00:17:35,520
"D"...?

217
00:17:37,190 --> 00:17:39,710
Who are you people?

218
00:17:42,560 --> 00:17:45,110
That question is a dead end, huh?

219
00:17:51,230 --> 00:17:52,380
I found you!

220
00:17:58,040 --> 00:17:59,520
Where is Princess Vivi?!

221
00:18:00,020 --> 00:18:01,130
Oh my...

222
00:18:02,140 --> 00:18:03,730
awake so soon?

223
00:18:04,660 --> 00:18:07,030
Now that I've got
a handle on your ability,

224
00:18:07,030 --> 00:18:09,280
this won't turn out like last time!

225
00:18:11,440 --> 00:18:14,820
Don't overexert yourself.
You must be seriously wounded.

226
00:18:20,750 --> 00:18:24,830
This works out perfectly.
Why don't you save that boy?

227
00:18:27,730 --> 00:18:34,260
He is the courageous knight who escorted
your precious princess to this land, after all.

228
00:18:35,090 --> 00:18:38,060
Besides, the princess is safe.

229
00:18:38,060 --> 00:18:40,300
She's currently heading to Alubarna.

230
00:18:40,300 --> 00:18:43,730
But I can't say what will happen to her now.

231
00:18:43,730 --> 00:18:45,730
It is what it is, you know?

232
00:18:59,890 --> 00:19:04,890
If I'm no match for her, then just
who will be able to protect Princess Vivi?

233
00:19:09,270 --> 00:19:12,010
M-Meat...!

234
00:19:13,110 --> 00:19:16,040
The final revolt has begun, has it?

235
00:19:16,710 --> 00:19:18,050
I saw their ship.

236
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:22,890
Princess Vivi and the others appear
to have arrived in this land safely.

237
00:19:22,890 --> 00:19:26,520
I must hurry. I do hope I am in time.

238
00:19:27,880 --> 00:19:29,900
Hey, are you all right?

239
00:19:29,900 --> 00:19:31,790
Meat...!

240
00:19:35,220 --> 00:19:37,100
Meat...!

241
00:19:37,100 --> 00:19:42,660
Meat? In your shape? What are
you talking about? Hang on.

242
00:19:43,190 --> 00:19:45,190
I will fetch a doctor.

243
00:19:48,130 --> 00:19:53,630
I'm gonna make Crocodile
pay for this...

244
00:19:55,900 --> 00:20:00,800
He made fun of Vivi...
and that dried-up old man...

245
00:20:01,360 --> 00:20:03,770
He's definitely gonna pay...

246
00:20:05,780 --> 00:20:08,230
Who are you?

247
00:20:09,450 --> 00:20:11,250
Meat...

248
00:20:32,540 --> 00:20:35,260
I see it! It's still far away,
but it's Alubarna!

249
00:20:37,150 --> 00:20:40,120
Koza, we're less than
thirty minutes away!

250
00:20:40,120 --> 00:20:41,260
Right!

251
00:20:41,260 --> 00:20:43,720
Alubarna is near!

252
00:20:43,720 --> 00:20:46,170
Raise your spirits!

253
00:20:50,960 --> 00:20:54,860
Commander Chaka! Rebel Army
due south, about fifteen klicks!

254
00:20:55,490 --> 00:20:59,010
Their army, two million strong,
is bearing down on the southern gate!

255
00:20:59,010 --> 00:21:02,820
East, west, south,
southeast, southwest...

256
00:21:02,820 --> 00:21:04,530
Defend each gate with your lives!

257
00:21:05,520 --> 00:21:08,520
Do not let them set foot in the city!

258
00:21:08,520 --> 00:21:09,710
Yes, sir!

259
00:21:25,140 --> 00:21:29,160
Look there! The Rebel Army is approaching!

260
00:21:29,160 --> 00:21:30,980
How fabulously many of them!

261
00:21:30,980 --> 00:21:35,040
The princess is quite
a nincompoop to try to stop them.

262
00:21:35,040 --> 00:21:39,440
But then, is the nincompoop
even coming?

263
00:21:39,440 --> 00:21:43,230
Or isn't she coming?
Is she coming? Or isn't she coming?

264
00:21:43,230 --> 00:21:44,320
It's so iffy!

265
00:21:44,320 --> 00:21:45,950
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey, hey!

266
00:21:45,950 --> 00:21:48,170
Are we sure of this?!
Are we sure of this?!

267
00:21:48,170 --> 00:21:50,920
The princess and the pirates
are really coming, no?!

268
00:21:50,920 --> 00:21:53,830
The Rebel Army is going
to get here first, at this rate!

269
00:21:53,830 --> 00:21:55,920
Good grief, are they even trying?!

270
00:21:56,440 --> 00:21:59,000
The chances of them
making it on time are low.

271
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:04,170
Here... they... come...

272
00:21:59,750 --> 00:22:04,170
After all, they lost quite
some time at Rainbase.

273
00:22:04,170 --> 00:22:05,390
What?! They did?!

274
00:22:06,580 --> 00:22:09,520
Well, supposing that
the rebellion starts first,

275
00:22:09,520 --> 00:22:12,140
what are we supposed to deux?

276
00:22:12,140 --> 00:22:15,120
We don't have to deux
anything, do we?

277
00:22:15,120 --> 00:22:19,820
Once the war starts, not even
the princess can do anything about it.

278
00:22:19,820 --> 00:22:23,590
We just need to get rid of
whoever we're told to get rid of.

279
00:22:23,590 --> 00:22:26,510
Can't you even conclude
that much for yourself?

280
00:22:26,510 --> 00:22:29,720
It sounds like you're just
dying for a taste of my kenpo!

281
00:22:29,720 --> 00:22:31,510
Knock it off, you two.

282
00:22:31,510 --> 00:22:33,800
Ah, my back! My back is aching!

283
00:22:33,800 --> 00:22:39,750
They... are... com... ing...

284
00:22:33,800 --> 00:22:36,750
Mr. 4, massage it for me!

285
00:22:39,750 --> 00:22:40,760
What?!

286
00:22:41,330 --> 00:22:44,380
Why didn't you tell us sooner,
you dim-witted daruma doll?!

287
00:22:47,220 --> 00:22:49,190
Ducks...?

288
00:22:50,220 --> 00:22:54,690
Ducks? What do you mean,
Miss Merry Christmas?

289
00:22:54,690 --> 00:22:57,980
Aren't there too many
of them? I see six people.

290
00:22:57,980 --> 00:23:02,110
There were four of them on that list,
not including Straw Hat, right?

291
00:23:02,580 --> 00:23:05,020
You're wrong, Miss Merry Christmas.

292
00:23:05,020 --> 00:23:09,570
Did you listen to what the boss said?
There's that Mr. Prince guy.

293
00:23:09,570 --> 00:23:13,620
And he wasn't working alone, so if
you add two, the numbers match up.

294
00:23:14,360 --> 00:23:17,290
Regardless of their number,
our only target is Vivi.

295
00:23:18,030 --> 00:23:20,070
What are you so anxious about?

296
00:23:20,800 --> 00:23:23,300
Mr. 1...

297
00:23:23,300 --> 00:23:26,590
You say that Vivi is the only
one we have to get rid of?

298
00:23:27,720 --> 00:23:29,050
Well then...

299
00:23:30,460 --> 00:23:33,020
You can guess which one is Vivi!

300
00:23:34,310 --> 00:23:36,520
They're all wearing the same cloak!

301
00:23:38,980 --> 00:23:41,320
And, those are
the fastest birds in Alabasta,

302
00:23:41,720 --> 00:23:43,280
giant spot-billed ducks!

303
00:23:48,270 --> 00:23:50,410
Why, those rotten...!

304
00:23:50,410 --> 00:23:53,330
Now how do we tell
which one is Vivi?!

305
00:23:53,330 --> 00:23:55,790
It's so iffy, you know!

306
00:23:55,790 --> 00:23:58,370
It's so iffy, you know!

307
00:23:58,370 --> 00:24:00,800
It's so iffy, you know!

308
00:24:06,160 --> 00:24:07,930
Let them have it, Mr. 4!

309
00:24:12,060 --> 00:24:13,060
Avoid it!

310
00:24:16,060 --> 00:24:19,020
They dodged it!
Those birds are fast, huh?

311
00:24:21,110 --> 00:24:23,860
Two of them broke off south!
They're splitting up!

312
00:24:23,860 --> 00:24:26,360
They're planning to go
to the south gate!

313
00:24:26,780 --> 00:24:29,300
That's directly toward the Rebel Army.

314
00:24:29,300 --> 00:24:32,080
Which means
that one of them is Vivi?

315
00:24:32,080 --> 00:24:34,620
We'll handle those two!

316
00:24:35,020 --> 00:24:36,790
Let's go, Mr. 4!

317
00:24:39,040 --> 00:24:42,000
Lethal Fire Star!

318
00:24:45,340 --> 00:24:49,430
Mr. 1, those two are breaking
off that way! That could be Vivi!

319
00:24:50,020 --> 00:24:52,470
They're planning to go
in through the west gate.

320
00:24:52,470 --> 00:24:54,600
Why, those...!

321
00:24:54,600 --> 00:24:56,140
After them!

322
00:24:57,770 --> 00:24:59,610
Un... deux!

323
00:24:59,610 --> 00:25:02,360
Okay, we're going
to the southwest gate!

324
00:25:05,810 --> 00:25:09,890
They can try for three of
Alubarna's five gates from the west.

325
00:25:10,390 --> 00:25:12,450
That group is heading that way, huh?

326
00:25:12,450 --> 00:25:14,870
Then we will too!
We'll wipe them out inside!

327
00:25:16,200 --> 00:25:18,500
You're not getting away!

328
00:25:22,960 --> 00:25:26,320
Hey, someone's coming up!
Is it the enemy?!

329
00:25:26,320 --> 00:25:27,420
No, wait!

330
00:25:27,420 --> 00:25:30,200
They're the Supersonic
Duck Squad! Let them in!

331
00:25:45,330 --> 00:25:48,710
There's no way you'll escape from me!

332
00:26:04,530 --> 00:26:07,210
Thanks for following us
all the way here!

333
00:26:07,210 --> 00:26:08,420
What?!

334
00:26:11,490 --> 00:26:13,260
Stop! Stop!

335
00:26:14,820 --> 00:26:18,570
You guys have good instincts!
That's right, I'm Princess Vivi!

336
00:26:18,570 --> 00:26:23,730
What's that cra—er—nonsense
you're talking about? I'm the real Vivi.

337
00:26:26,350 --> 00:26:28,800
I wonder if this is far enough?

338
00:26:33,220 --> 00:26:36,870
It's amusing how well you fell for it.

339
00:26:37,410 --> 00:26:38,200
Now...

340
00:26:39,080 --> 00:26:41,710
let us show you who we really are.

341
00:26:42,960 --> 00:26:45,880
– Too bad, you guessed wrong!
– Too bad, you guessed wrong!

342
00:26:49,860 --> 00:26:52,220
What?!

343
00:26:57,870 --> 00:26:59,930
Thank you, everyone.

344
00:27:02,420 --> 00:27:06,520
I have to hurry. The Rebel Army
could arrive at any moment.

345
00:27:07,390 --> 00:27:08,820
Let's go, Karoo!

346
00:27:10,530 --> 00:27:12,190
A camel?!

347
00:27:12,190 --> 00:27:15,450
And I know you from earlier!

348
00:27:15,450 --> 00:27:17,160
S-Sorry!

349
00:27:17,160 --> 00:27:19,160
Go on, Zoro! Let them have it!

350
00:27:19,160 --> 00:27:21,350
You keep quiet!

351
00:27:21,350 --> 00:27:23,120
They got us.

352
00:27:21,350 --> 00:27:23,120
How much was that debt, again?

353
00:27:23,120 --> 00:27:25,330
Quite the farce, huh?

354
00:27:23,120 --> 00:27:25,330
You've already forgiven that!

355
00:27:26,830 --> 00:27:29,460
There won't be a rebellion now.

356
00:27:29,460 --> 00:27:31,050
What?!

357
00:27:34,300 --> 00:27:35,930
I'll stop them, at any cost!

358
00:27:35,930 --> 00:27:39,380
If I don't stop them now,
then this will all be for naught!

359
00:27:41,940 --> 00:27:47,290
Vivi and Koza must not
be allowed to meet!

360
00:27:54,060 --> 00:27:57,300
Secure those cannonballs!
I don't want them rolling away!

361
00:27:57,300 --> 00:27:59,500
Artillerymen, maintain your posts!

362
00:27:59,500 --> 00:28:02,040
Keep your cannonballs
under tight control!

363
00:28:02,790 --> 00:28:04,790
The ground is really rumbling, huh?

364
00:28:04,790 --> 00:28:07,790
The enemy is a force
of two million angry men.

365
00:28:07,790 --> 00:28:11,250
Even the earth trembles
before them. Do not shrink back!

366
00:28:22,460 --> 00:28:25,500
It's okay, Karoo.
You don't have to be here.

367
00:28:28,520 --> 00:28:30,730
We wouldn't want you
to get trampled.

368
00:28:42,630 --> 00:28:47,370
Please, Leader,
listen to what I have to say.

369
00:28:53,380 --> 00:28:57,630
Everyone, stay together!
Charge through at the south gate!

370
00:28:57,630 --> 00:29:00,550
We'll knock out all
the others from the inside!

371
00:29:00,550 --> 00:29:02,840
Be steadfast in your resolve!

372
00:29:11,520 --> 00:29:13,690
Stop, Rebel Army!

373
00:29:13,690 --> 00:29:16,440
This fight is a setup!

374
00:29:19,450 --> 00:29:21,860
Please! Listen to me!

375
00:29:27,290 --> 00:29:29,160
Rebel Army! Stop–

376
00:29:34,610 --> 00:29:37,850
Hey, did you see a person
there just now?

377
00:29:37,850 --> 00:29:39,420
A person? Don't be absurd!

378
00:29:39,420 --> 00:29:42,620
Never mind that,
they're already shooting at us!

379
00:29:46,460 --> 00:29:50,520
Why did they...?
We can't see anything now!

380
00:29:53,000 --> 00:29:56,480
What kind of foolish move
was that, Royal Army?

381
00:29:56,770 --> 00:30:00,450
You idiot! I haven't given
the order to fire yet!

382
00:30:00,450 --> 00:30:03,120
Don't go acting on your own!

383
00:30:03,120 --> 00:30:08,250
T-Terribly sorry about that! My hand
slipped, and it just happened.

384
00:30:27,980 --> 00:30:31,230
Don't back down! Charge through!
It's just a cloud of sand!

385
00:30:32,290 --> 00:30:34,730
No, everyone! Stop!

386
00:30:35,710 --> 00:30:39,190
For the sake of our country!
Make the king pay!

387
00:30:39,190 --> 00:30:40,280
Leader!

388
00:30:50,370 --> 00:30:52,120
Leader!

389
00:30:59,580 --> 00:31:00,760
What's wrong, Koza?

390
00:31:02,250 --> 00:31:04,430
It's nothing.

391
00:31:06,160 --> 00:31:07,680
Was it my imagination?

392
00:31:21,560 --> 00:31:22,870
Leader!

393
00:31:24,860 --> 00:31:27,820
Remember, this is our final battle!

394
00:31:30,330 --> 00:31:32,290
Wait! Listen to me!

395
00:31:34,750 --> 00:31:36,710
Leader!

396
00:31:53,720 --> 00:31:55,730
Here they come!

397
00:31:55,730 --> 00:31:58,390
Prepare to fire!

398
00:32:24,600 --> 00:32:28,380
Bring down Alubarna!

399
00:33:00,890 --> 00:33:01,880
Karoo...

400
00:33:05,590 --> 00:33:08,220
You shielded me...

401
00:33:11,390 --> 00:33:18,910
I'm so sorry... Even after all this,
the rebellion has begun.

402
00:33:18,910 --> 00:33:20,850
I'm so sorry...

403
00:33:22,050 --> 00:33:24,350
But still, I will stop it!

404
00:33:24,350 --> 00:33:26,410
No matter how often
they knock me down,

405
00:33:26,410 --> 00:33:30,660
I can't let something like this
undo all we have accomplished.

406
00:33:30,660 --> 00:33:34,900
That's something I learned
aboard that ship—

407
00:33:36,190 --> 00:33:38,300
not knowing when to quit!

408
00:33:40,700 --> 00:33:41,790
Vivi!

409
00:33:43,710 --> 00:33:45,310
So this is where you are!

410
00:33:45,310 --> 00:33:46,750
Usopp!

411
00:33:46,750 --> 00:33:49,970
We can still make it in time!
Hurry up and hop on!

412
00:33:49,970 --> 00:33:52,180
Right! Hold on, Karoo...

413
00:33:52,180 --> 00:33:54,180
There's no saving that bird!

414
00:33:56,370 --> 00:34:00,760
Come on now! The rebellion
will only get worse! Hurry!

415
00:34:03,100 --> 00:34:06,110
That... bird...?

416
00:34:09,530 --> 00:34:11,700
Let's go, Karoo!

417
00:34:15,990 --> 00:34:19,330
What's the matter? Quickly! This way!

418
00:34:21,790 --> 00:34:24,760
Usopp, prove yourself.

419
00:34:27,110 --> 00:34:30,380
Oh, you doubt who I am?

420
00:34:31,510 --> 00:34:32,340
See?

421
00:34:32,340 --> 00:34:33,620
No!

422
00:34:35,300 --> 00:34:38,410
Usopp! Hey, Usopp!

423
00:34:38,410 --> 00:34:40,270
Eyelashes, wake up!

424
00:34:41,140 --> 00:34:44,970
Oh, Sanji. Good morning.

425
00:34:43,890 --> 00:34:44,970
Right.

426
00:34:44,970 --> 00:34:47,780
Ah, how did our fight turn out?

427
00:34:47,780 --> 00:34:51,310
The part of the mission where we
lured them away was successful.

428
00:34:51,310 --> 00:34:52,280
And then...

429
00:34:52,280 --> 00:34:56,280
it was over in two seconds.
One second each.

430
00:34:56,280 --> 00:34:58,200
Did you even try?!

431
00:35:00,370 --> 00:35:02,120
But Sanji, what are you doing here?

432
00:35:02,120 --> 00:35:05,920
Your ducks came to get you help! But...

433
00:35:04,950 --> 00:35:05,920
I see.

434
00:35:06,710 --> 00:35:08,860
You let Mr. 2 get away, didn't you?

435
00:35:08,860 --> 00:35:09,880
Yes.

436
00:35:15,050 --> 00:35:19,360
Listen up. That freak's
transformations are perfect.

437
00:35:19,360 --> 00:35:24,100
He could impersonate any one of us
and make an attempt on Vivi's life.

438
00:35:24,100 --> 00:35:27,060
If you think anyone is acting
the least bit suspicious,

439
00:35:30,020 --> 00:35:32,530
take off your bandage
and confirm your marks.

440
00:35:32,530 --> 00:35:34,530
If someone can't do that,
they're a fake.

441
00:35:35,040 --> 00:35:40,200
Whoa, taking precautions like that
is oddly savvy of you.

442
00:35:40,730 --> 00:35:43,450
So does that mean
you're that freak already?!

443
00:35:43,450 --> 00:35:44,830
I'll cut you down!

444
00:35:44,830 --> 00:35:46,350
Ah, it's Zoro.

445
00:35:46,350 --> 00:35:48,420
Oh, it really is Zoro?

446
00:35:54,630 --> 00:35:57,840
You... are not Usopp!

447
00:36:00,030 --> 00:36:01,810
Oh, dear...

448
00:36:03,310 --> 00:36:06,770
I wonder what gave me away.

449
00:36:06,770 --> 00:36:09,400
I thought it was perfect.

450
00:36:10,530 --> 00:36:13,720
We got a report that you
all had the same wrapping,

451
00:36:13,720 --> 00:36:17,200
straight from Zero baby.

452
00:36:18,880 --> 00:36:21,200
This is bad.

453
00:36:21,730 --> 00:36:23,960
Vivi is in danger!

